description.narrative: As two major cyclones hit the country the UNICEF Mozambique advocacy and communication work had to change priorities in the beginning of the year and follow the L3 emergency response and recovery work. With support from the regional office in Nairobi, the media hub in Johannesburg, as well as DOC and PFP the UNICEF Mozambique bundled its communication and advocacy resources to respond to the global media interest, to contribute to the fundraising for the emergency response and to showcase the responsible use of funds received for the disasters. Despite the humanitarian crisis regular advocacy and communication work also continued. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:12/12/2019
